description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Patient Safety Lead who will work within the DHU Health Care CIC Clinical Governance department, to lead on the management of patient feedback/concerns and Health Care Professional Feedback (HCPF) and support in the development and dissemination of the Patient Safety and Risk Strategy within the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, you should have the following:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinical professional qualification – first level registered nurse, other allied health professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree or equivalent qualification or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent standard of written and oral English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Three years working at a senior level in a health provider organisation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two years’ experience in an NHS clinical or clinical governance / quality / risk management role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in the use of computerised systems including Microsoft Office&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organisational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective diary &amp; time management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible &amp; adaptable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work effectively with a wide range of professional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work occasional evenings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to travel to Leicester, Derby and other DHU LLR urgent care sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work at strategic and operational level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to collect, understand, analyse and summarise qualitative and numerical data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creative problem solving with the ability to think laterally&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to prepare reports for a variety of audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for all the above, we offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous holiday entitlement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Pension Scheme membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work independently to encourage a patient safety culture within DHU&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours of work are 37.5hrs on a permanent basis, with a competitive salary of £32,000.00-£36,000.00 depending on experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rosalind Kibble, Corporate Head of Clinical/ Integrated Governance, rosalind.kibble@dhuhealthcare.nhs.uk, 0300 1000 404&lt;/p&gt;
